================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

Reverie's optional native backend sources are referenced as git submodules
under `third-party/`. These submodules use `update = none` and are not fetched
by a normal clone or Cargo build. No source or binaries from these projects are
redistributed in this repository; only pinned submodule commit references are
stored here. See `docs/BACKEND_SOURCES.md` for explicit activation commands.

Building reverie-dbi after explicitly activating DynamoRIO builds DynamoRIO
and, transitively, the third-party projects that DynamoRIO itself vendors as
submodules. The licenses of those components are summarized below. This NOTICE
is provided for attribution and awareness; the authoritative and complete
license texts live in each upstream project. Anyone who *distributes* binaries
produced from this build must comply with all of the licenses listed here,
including the copyleft (LGPL) obligations noted for elfutils and certain
DynamoRIO extensions.

